  "text": "Human LDL (1.019 Ͻ d Ͻ 1.063 g/ml), high-density lipoprotein (HDL) 3 fraction (1.125 Ͻ d Ͻ 1.210 g/ml) and lipoprotein-defi cient serum (LPDS, d Ͼ 1.125 g/ml) were prepared from plasma of healthy human subjects and isolated by differential ultracentrifugation as described previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The lipoprotein fractions were dialyzed intensively against phosphate buffered saline (PBS, pH 7.4) containing 150 mM NaCl and 0.3 mM ethylene diaminetetraacetic acid (EDTA). In order to generate oxLDL, plasma LDL (3 mg apo B/ml) was extensively dialyzed against PBS (pH 7.4) containing 150 mM NaCl and 5 µM EDTA and then incubated with 10 µM CuSO 4 for 18 h at 37 °C. Its modifi cation was verifi ed by its mobility on agarose gel electrophoresis (Paragon, Beckman Instruments). All lipoprotein fractions were fi ltered through a 0.2 µM Millipore membrane and stored at 4 °C.",
